        "HHRD's financial health is anchored by its ability to scale while maintaining low overhead. With <cite id=\"2\">$94,048,415 in revenue</cite> and a <cite id=\"11\">3-year revenue CAGR of 8.2%</cite>, the organization shows steady growth. Its governance is equally strong, featuring a <cite id=\"12\">10-member board with 100% independent members</cite>. This oversight supports a massive global reach, including <cite id=\"13\">$8,817,000 in foreign grants</cite> distributed to local implementing partners and direct service programs in crisis zones."
      ],
      "summary": "Helping Hand for Relief and Development (HHRD) is an international humanitarian organization that has been <cite id=\"1\">serving humanity since 1998</cite> by integrating resources for people in need. The organization operates at a significant scale, reporting <cite id=\"2\">total revenue of $94,048,415</cite> in its most recent fiscal year. HHRD is distinguished by its exceptional financial management, maintaining <cite id=\"3\">a perfect 100/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite>, which reflects its commitment to accountability and transparency. The charity's operational model is highly efficient, with a <cite id=\"4\">program expense ratio of 91.2%</cite>, ensuring that the vast majority of donor contributions directly fund its global initiatives. These programs span a wide range of critical needs, including <cite id=\"5\">orphan support, healthcare, and emergency disaster response</cite> in regions such as Pakistan, Jordan, and Haiti. Furthermore, HHRD demonstrates high fundraising efficiency, spending only <cite id=\"6\">$0.06 to raise every $1</cite> in contributions. As a <cite id=\"7\">zakat-eligible organization</cite>, it serves as a primary vehicle for Muslim donors to fulfill their religious obligations through verified channels that support the poor, the needy, and those in debt.",
